      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAILOR'S RUM (2) scored at his most recent appearance, getting home by 2.25 lengths over 1000m at Emerald as favourite. That continued the solid form this campaign, with three wins and two minor placings from seven runs. Top chance again. INQUISITIVE LEGEND (5) found the line nicely last start to get up for third over 1100m at Longreach. Generally goes well here and is expected to run a big race. ICHIBERU (8) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1100m at Longreach, beaten 4.5 lengths into sixth after being prominent at the corner. Finds a nice race and can play a significant role in the outcome. BLANC DE NOIR (10) ran below expectations last time at Julia Creek, finishing eighth and beaten 5.5 lengths. Should be in the mix in this more suitable race.",
